         <abstract encodinganalog="5203_">The Matilda Benyesh-Melnick, MD papers document the career of Dr. Mailda Benyesh-Melnick, who made significant contributions to the fields of virology, microbiology, and oncology before beginning her career as a psychiatrist. She worked closely with her husband, Joseph L. Melnick, MD on his research on poliomyelitis as well as conducting her own research in myoplasma and it's relationship with cancer development in certain animals. This collection focuses on the research she conducted and collected between 1956 and 1974. The collection consists of 2 boxes, equaling .75 cubic feet. It contains reprints, reports, journals, magazines, and an undated manuscript. The materials are in good condition.<!--Very brief summary of collection contents 
